meanings.definition: To walk with long steps or strides, especially in a confident or aggressive manner.
meanings.sent1: The determined athlete outstrode his competitors to win the race.
meanings.sent2: She outstrode confidently into the meeting room, ready to present her ideas.
meanings.sent3: The little dog outstrode the big ones, surprising everyone with its speed.
meanings.sent4: With unwavering determination, she outstrode all obstacles in her path.
meanings.sent5: His outstrode gait left a lasting impression on everyone who witnessed it.
